Purchase options and add-ons

  • Introducing Stare! Junior, a proud recipient of the National Parenting Center Seal and the Teacher's Choice Award for Families! This engaging game captivates children by enhancing their observational, memory, and reading skills all while having a blast.
  • Featuring unique image cards, Stare! Junior puts kids' observation abilities to the test. Players have 30 seconds to examine a card's image and memorize as much detail as possible. With a delightful variety of illustrations, photos, animations, and comics, there's never a dull moment!
  • Once time is up, players answer fun questions about the image, such as: What color is the girl's birthday hat? How many party gifts is the boy holding? Whats on top of the classroom desk? Each correct answer moves them closer to the winners circle on the game board.
  • To level the playing field, the game can be adjusted for different age groups. While kids have 30 seconds to stare, adults will only have 10 seconds, allowing everyone to compete at their best level. This entertaining and educational experience is the perfect addition to family game night!
  • Ready for some fun? Click the Stare Junior video to see the game in action! Designed to educate and entertain, Stare! Junior is ideal for children ages 6-8 and 8-12, and its enjoyable for adults and parents as well!
  • [A Quick Note: This latest edition of Stare! Junior features an all new collection of image cards and has received multiple awards. References to editions printed before (c) 2007 pertain to earlier, out-of-print versions of the game. You can find the most recent 2025(c) print date on the lower left-hand corner of the boxs back.]

  3. Describe GDG Games in one sentence:

    Creators of Timeless Board Games - Designing Fun & Sparking Thought

    What does "Designing Fun & Sparking Thought" mean?

    It means making games that are both enjoyable and mentally engaging. We want our games to challenge your thinking, while still providing the kind of fun that keeps you coming back.

    How do you strike the balance between fun and thought?

    Every game we create is designed so that fun and smart elements are intertwined. Youll have those laugh-out-loud moments, those wait, what? surprises, and that irresistible urge to play again and again.

  4. What makes a game "timeless"?

    A timeless game is one that doesnt feel stale, no matter how many times you play it. Its the kind of game that keeps offering new challenges and laughs each time you pull it out.

    Why is sparking thought important?

    We really love designing games that make you think, not just play. Having said that, we love our good light hearted fun games too!

    Whats the secret to your game design philosophy?

    Our focus is on creating an experience thats both fun and smart. We believe a game should be more than a one-time experienceit should be a lifelong keeper.

  5. Any media reviews of your games?

    GDG Games has enjoyed high praise from top outlets including: Readers Digest, The New York Times (Wirecutter), Variety, Oprah Daily, Rolling Stone, Country Living (and many more).

    What are some of the headlines?

    Featured in: "24 Classic Games Everyone Should Own" (Reader's Digest), "Best Games for Kids" (Scripps), "Best Trivia Games..." (Oprah Daily), "19 Super Fun Adult Games..." (Country Living) and many more.

    Any awards?

    Yes! A variety of our games are award winners, including: National Parenting Center Seal, Teacher's Choice Award, Game of the Year and more!

Product description

  • In STARE! JUNIOR board game, kids test and train their visual memory skills and have a blast doing it! Players have 30 seconds to stare at an image on a card. Images are varied and fun for kids to look at. It might be an illustration, funny photo, comic, animation and more. When time is up, an opponent will flip over the card and ask the player a series of questions about the image to see how much they can recall. What is the clown holding in his left hand? What color is the boy's birthday party hat? How many gifts are on top of the table? Guess right and advance on the game board. Kids can play individually or in teams. There are special rules for parents too! You can also adjust for different levels of play - while kids are given 30 seconds, parents can be given only 10 seconds. This allows all age groups to compete together at their own best level. Great for family game night! Includes image cards, game board, sand timer, playing pieces, die and instructions.

    How customer reviews and ratings work

    Customer Reviews, including Product Star Ratings help customers to learn more about the product and decide whether it is the right product for them.

    To calculate the overall star rating and percentage breakdown by star, we dont use a simple average. Instead, our system considers things like how recent a review is and if the reviewer bought the item on Amazon. It also analyzed reviews to verify trustworthiness.

    • JV
      5.0 out of 5 stars Great game
      Reviewed in the United States on May 8, 2017
      Verified Purchase
      Very fun game. We bought this as a gift for our neices. From what I remember, you look at a picture and try to remember as much about it as possible before the time is up (30 seconds?). Then you roll the dice and another person asks you a question on the back of the card that corresponds with the same number you rolled. If you get the question right, you can move your token that many spaces. You keep rolling and answering questions until you either get an answer wrong or you roll the same number you already rolled in that turn. Whoever reaches the end of the board first wins. The only thing in the directions we disregarded was that adults get less time. Why??? The game is already difficult enough for adults to be giving more limitations. The game comes with tons of cards so there is a lot of gameplay without duplication. I have a bad memory when it comes to standard memory games or remembering groups of words so I wasn't sure if I'd like it, but the pictures are zany enough that they were memorable and I actually did decently. One thing i didn't like is that your turn is over if you roll the same number you already rolled. I lost due to that (maybe I'm just a sore loser). I think I'll most likely buy this game for my son when he's older as well.

      Reviewed in the United States on February 6, 2012
      Verified Purchase
      Our family enjoys this game, we even include our 3 year old.

      When our 3 year old has her turn she gets a card picked with no reading required. Then we ask her the question on the card or we make up a question that is age appropriate and she does amazingly well. For example just ask you child what color a character was wearing or hat was.

      This works well for us as we can be challenged and it keeps our minds sharp and the little one can play too. We all have fun.

      Its pretty funny to play as a adult and you get some cards that you wonder if you will remember anything, it will get you laughing at yourself!

      My only cons are this. Cards are a bit small I feel like I need glasses to play. Cards do bend easy so durability isn't that high. I wish the playing pieces were weighted a bit more so the didn't get knocked off the board so easily.

      But I wouldn't let that stop me from buying this again.
